casebody.data:
COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. McGINN ESTATE COMPANY, Respondent. No. 7601. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 29, 1934. Frank J. Wideman, Asst. Atty. Gen., and Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. John L. McGinn, of San Francisco, Cal., for respondent.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for petitioner, consented to by counsel for respondent, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
